claim.claim-text:
1. An implantable lead electrode assembly for implantation in the torso of a patient, the assembly comprising:
an electrode having a proximal end, a distal end, first and second lateral portions, and front and back sides, the front side adapted for sliding insertion over the patient's ribcage;
a first insertion tool receiver secured relative the first lateral portion of the electrode;
a second insertion tool receiver secured relative the second lateral portion of the electrode; and
a cover assembly, the cover assembly defining the first insertion tool receiver;
wherein the cover assembly includes a front portion and a back portion, the front portion defining a skirt covering a portion of the front side of the electrode, the back portion disposed adjacent a portion of the back side of the electrode, the assembly further including securing means for securing the front portion and the back portion together on opposing sides of the electrode.

16. An implantable device system comprising:
an implantable housing containing circuitry adapted to provide electrical stimulus to alleviate cardiac disorders;
an electrode lead assembly including:
an electrode having a proximal end, a distal end, first and second lateral portions, and front and back sides;
a lead for electrically coupling the electrode to the housing;
a first insertion tool receiver secured relative the first lateral portion of the electrode; and
a second insertion tool receiver secured relative the second lateral portion of the electrode; and

an insertion tool including tines having fixed spacing to be receieved in the insertion tool receivers.
